    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  Observational studies have suggested that having coronary artery disease increases the risk of Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) susceptibility and severity, but it remains unclear if this association is causal. Inferring causation is critical to facilitate the development of appropriate policies and/or individual decisions to reduce the incidence and burden of COVID-19. We applied Two-sample Mendelian randomization analysis and found that genetically predicted CAD was significantly associated with higher risk of COVID-19: the odds ratio was 1.29 (95% confidence interval 1.11 to 1.49;\n                  <jats:italic>P</jats:italic>\n                  = 0.001) per unit higher log odds of having CAD.\n                </jats:p>",
